denmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/25/why-did-deep-throat-leak-to-woodward/#respond\" title=\"Comment on Why Did Deep Throat Leak to&nbsp;Woodward?\">Leave a Comment</a></p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"entry-categories tagged\">Filed under <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/america-2/\" title=\"View all posts in America\" rel=\"category tag\">America</a>, <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/journalism/\" title=\"View all posts in Journalism\" rel=\"category tag\">Journalism</a></p>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"entry-tags tagged\">Tagged as <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/tag/watergate/\" rel=\"tag\">watergate</a><br /></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-links -->\n\n</div><!-- #post-## -->\n\n\n\n<div id=\"post-5186\" class=\"post-5186 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-america-2 category-berlin-2 category-germany category-personal tag-complaining tag-sundays\">\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\n\t\tFebruary 23, 2012 &middot; 4:00 pm\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\n\t<h2 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/\" rel=\"bookmark\">I Live in a Socialist&nbsp;Dystopia</a></h2>\t<div class=\"entry entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>From a <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/23/business/global/in-germany-a-limp-domestic-economy-stifled-by-regulation.html\">NYTimes article</a> on Germany&#8217;s palsied domestic economy:</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\"><em>Now, German states can set their own shop hours, and most have lifted restrictions during the workweek â€” though Sunday is still taboo in most places. Florists and bakers are typically allowed to open a few hours on Sunday.</em></p>\n<p>I cannot express how frustrating it is to live in a country where everything is closed on Sundays. I mean <em>everything</em>. Books, clothing, furniture, electronics, groceries: These are the things you will do without for fully 50% of your weekly non-working days.</p>\n<p>When I first moved to Europe, I thought this would be something I would get used to eventually, like paying for plastic bags or Â headlice outbreaks. But at least once per week I have the same inner monologue:</p>\n<p>&#8216;I need [household item]. I&#8217;d better stop at the store on the way home. Oh wait, it&#8217;s Sunday. &#8230; I&#8217;ll just do without that until <em>next fucking Saturday.</em>&#8216;</p>\n<p>The fact that florists and bakers are the only shops allowed to be open on Sundays somehow makes this even more insulting. It&#8217;s like the government is saying,Â <em>We accept that human beings need items to live, including on Sundays. But we will only allow you to purchase supplies for government-approved weekend activities</em>.</p>\n<p>So if you want to read the newspaper, eat a croissant and fluff some tulips on a Sunday, the government will support you. If you want to fix your bike, get a prescription filled, buy furniture or make an actual meal, the government will Â thwart you.</p>\n<p>So enjoy it, America. Next time you wake up on a Sunday, buy a loaf of bread and make toast, you&#8217;re tasting freedom.</p>\n<div id=\"jp-post-flair\" class=\"sharedaddy sd-like-enabled sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing\"><h3 class=\"sd-title\">Share this:</h3><div class=\"sd-content\"><ul><li class=\"share-facebook\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-facebook sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share on Facebook\" id=\"sharing-facebook-5186\"><span>Facebook</span></a></li><li class=\"share-twitter\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-twitter sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=twitter\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Twitter\" id=\"sharing-twitter-5186\"><span>Twitter</span></a></li><li class=\"share-tumblr\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-tumblr sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=tumblr\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Tumblr\"><span>Tumblr</span></a></li><li class=\"share-reddit\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-reddit sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=reddit\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Reddit\"><span>Reddit</span></a></li><li class=\"share-stumbleupon\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-stumbleupon sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=stumbleupon\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on StumbleUpon\"><span>StumbleUpon</span></a></li><li class=\"share-email\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-email sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=email\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to email this to a friend\"><span>Email</span></a></li><li><a href=\"#\" class=\"sharing-anchor sd-button share-more\"><span>More</span></a></li><li class=\"share-end\"></li></ul><div class=\"sharing-hidden\"><div class=\"inner\" style=\"display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"share-google-plus-1\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-google-plus-1 sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=google-plus-1\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Google+\" id=\"sharing-google-5186\"><span>Google</span></a></li><li class=\"share-digg\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-digg sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=digg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to Digg this post\"><span>Digg</span></a></li><li class=\"share-end\"></li><li class=\"share-print\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-print sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to print\"><span>Print</span></a></li><li class=\"share-linkedin\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-linkedin sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/?share=linkedin\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on LinkedIn\" id=\"sharing-linkedin-5186\"><span>LinkedIn</span></a></li><li class=\"share-end\"></li><li class=\"share-end\"></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-15624535-5186-52f48118cbcd7' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=15624535&amp;post_id=5186&amp;origin=rottenindenmark.wordpress.com&amp;obj_id=15624535-5186-52f48118cbcd7' data-name='like-post-frame-15624535-5186-52f48118cbcd7'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height:55px'><span class='button'><span>Like</span></span> <span class=\"loading\">Loading...</span></div><span class='sd-text-color'></span><a class='sd-link-color'></a></div></div>\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\t\n\t<div class=\"entry-links\">\n\t\t<p class=\"comment-number\"><a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/23/i-live-in-a-socialist-dystopia/#comments\" title=\"Comment on I Live in a Socialist&nbsp;Dystopia\">2 Comments</a></p>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"entry-categories tagged\">Filed under <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/america-2/\" title=\"View all posts in America\" rel=\"category tag\">America</a>, <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/berlin-2/\" title=\"View all posts in Berlin\" rel=\"category tag\">Berlin</a>, <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/germany/\" title=\"View all posts in Germany\" rel=\"category tag\">Germany</a>, <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/category/personal/\" title=\"View all posts in Personal\" rel=\"category tag\">Personal</a></p>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"entry-tags tagged\">Tagged as <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/tag/complaining/\" rel=\"tag\">complaining</a>, <a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/tag/sundays/\" rel=\"tag\">sundays</a><br /></p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-links -->\n\n</div><!-- #post-## -->\n\n\n\n<div id=\"post-5179\" class=\"post-5179 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-journalism tag-links\">\n\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\n\t\tFebruary 17, 2012 &middot; 10:21 am\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\n\t<h2 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/\" rel=\"bookmark\">The &#8216;Crying At My Laptop&#8217; Literary&nbsp;Playlist</a></h2>\t<div class=\"entry entry-content\">\n\t\t<p>I read so many good articles this week! Here&#8217;s what I concluded about the world on their basis:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/social-issues/interrupters/i-see-everything-through-this-tragedy/\">Chicago schoolkids have post-traumatic stress</a> because they basically live in Chechnya.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.boston.com/ae/music/articles/2012/02/07/why_does_adeles_grammy_nominated_someone_like_you_make_people_cry/?page=full\">Adele makes you cry</a> because her music is engineered to make her sound vulnerable and alone, just like you.</li>\n<li>The University of Phoenix peddles highly subsidized <a href=\"http://www.harpers.org/archive/2011/10/0083639\">educational snake oil</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?expire&amp;urlID=425607593&amp;action=cpt&amp;partnerID=289881\">Gareth Thomas is the world&#8217;s only openly gay maleÂ athlete</a>. He is also charming, tragic, inspiring and <a href=\"http://randyreport.blogspot.com/2012/01/gareth-thomas-to-join-big-brother-uk.html\">hot as breakfast</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.believermag.com/issues/201202/?read=article_bobrow-strain\">Industrial-scale breadmaking</a> is fluffy and gross.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1194725/1/index.htm\">Wrestling is interesting</a> when combined with terminal illness.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2012/03/diner-201203\"><em>Diner</em> changed the world</a>, even though none of your friends have heard of it.</li>\n<li>New York is the only city in America where customers will tolerate a <a href=\"http://nymag.com/print/?/nymetro/shopping/features/11908/\">shitty retail experience</a> in the name of convenience.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/1969/12/obama-explained/8874/?single_page=true\">Hillary was right </a>about Obama.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All of these deal with super-sad subject matter, but they&#8217;re so inspiringly well-written, you almost forget how depressing they are.</p>\n<div id=\"jp-post-flair\" class=\"sharedaddy sd-like-enabled sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled\"><div class=\"robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing\"><h3 class=\"sd-title\">Share this:</h3><div class=\"sd-content\"><ul><li class=\"share-facebook\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-facebook sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=facebook\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Share on Facebook\" id=\"sharing-facebook-5179\"><span>Facebook</span></a></li><li class=\"share-twitter\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-twitter sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=twitter\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Twitter\" id=\"sharing-twitter-5179\"><span>Twitter</span></a></li><li class=\"share-tumblr\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-tumblr sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=tumblr\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Tumblr\"><span>Tumblr</span></a></li><li class=\"share-reddit\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-reddit sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=reddit\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Reddit\"><span>Reddit</span></a></li><li class=\"share-stumbleupon\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-stumbleupon sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=stumbleupon\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on StumbleUpon\"><span>StumbleUpon</span></a></li><li class=\"share-email\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-email sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=email\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to email this to a friend\"><span>Email</span></a></li><li><a href=\"#\" class=\"sharing-anchor sd-button share-more\"><span>More</span></a></li><li class=\"share-end\"></li></ul><div class=\"sharing-hidden\"><div class=\"inner\" style=\"display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"share-google-plus-1\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-google-plus-1 sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=google-plus-1\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to share on Google+\" id=\"sharing-google-5179\"><span>Google</span></a></li><li class=\"share-digg\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"share-digg sd-button share-icon\" href=\"https://rottenindenmark.wordpress.com/2012/02/17/the-crying-at-my-laptop-literary-playlist/?share=digg\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Click to Digg this post\"><span>Digg